headline: Veralto (NYSE:VLTO) Reports Q3 In Line With Expectations
summary: Water analytics and treatment company Veralto (NYSE:VLTO) met Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q3 CY2025, with sales up 6.8% year on year to $1.40 billion. On the other hand, next quarter’s revenue guidance of $1.38 billion was less impressive, coming in 1.4% below analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.99 per share was 4.6% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Veralto (VLTO) Q3 Earnings and Revenues Beat Estimates
summary: Veralto (VLTO) delivered earnings and revenue surprises of +4.21% and +0.58%, respectively, for the quarter ended September 2025. Do the numbers hold clues to what lies ahead for the stock?

headline: Veralto: Q3 Earnings Snapshot
summary: The results topped Wall Street expectations. The average estimate of four analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was for earnings of 95 cents per share. The water and product quality services provider posted revenue of $1.4 billion in the period, which matched Street forecasts.
